# Tessera Patch Rules

## Methodology

Follow the 7-phase lifecycle: analyse → define → explore → implement → test → record → reconcile

## CLI Commands

- `tpatch init` — Initialize .tpatch/ workspace
- `tpatch add <description>` — Create feature request
- `tpatch status` — Feature status dashboard
- `tpatch analyze <slug>` — Run analysis phase
- `tpatch define <slug>` — Generate acceptance criteria
- `tpatch explore <slug>` — Explore codebase
- `tpatch implement <slug>` — Generate apply recipe
- `tpatch apply <slug>` — Execute recipe or record session
- `tpatch record <slug>` — Capture patches
- `tpatch reconcile` — Reconcile with upstream
- `tpatch provider check` — Validate provider
- `tpatch config show|set` — Manage configuration

## Data Location

All feature data is in `.tpatch/features/<slug>/`. Check `status.json` for current state.

## Safety

- Never write outside the repository root
- Store auth tokens in env vars, reference by name in config
- Review apply recipes before executing
